(If deemed inadvisable to run this race over the turf course, it will be run on the Tapeta Course at One Mile and Seventy Yards) (Rail at 42 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CALLING ALL ANGELS (IRE) stalked inside of rivals around the first turn and was in the two path down the backstretch, was under light rousing while waiting for an opening around the far turn, tipped out to the five path into the stretch, bid going into the final furlong, and drew past the inner pacesetter in the final sixteenth to win. RUN FOR COVER brushed with an inner foe at the start, set the pace in the two path, was roused while floating out to the four path turning into the stretch, and stayed on through the stretch but was caught by an outer foe late to finish with place. ALHAAN got bumped between foes leaving the gate, was in the two path around the first turn and rated in the three path down the backstretch, was driven in the four path around the far turn, and tipped in to the three path after a right handed cue at the top of the lane, and kept on down the lane inside of foes to get up for show late. OOPSIE DOOPSIE was up close while in range in the four path around the first turn and was in the five path down the backside, received a right handed cue while tipping out to the six path into the stretch, and finished evenly. GREY PRINCESS race in midpack under a hold in the four path, was ridden in the five path around the far turn and angled out to the eighth path for the stretch, but evened out in the final furlong. IRISH UNION traveled off the pace in three path around the first turn and trailed in the four path down the backstretch, was driven around the far turn and swung out to the nine path into the stretch, passed tired rivals down the center but was no factor. MAGIC CALL was unhurried in the two path, under coaxing around the far turn while floating out to the five path into the lane, and never threatened. SING SCAT prompted the pace in the three path around the first turn, was roused into the far turn, shifted out to the seven path while under a ride into the lane, but flattened. D CITY GIRL brushed with an outer foe just after the start, race in midfield around the two path but faded turning into the stretch. SAMURAI'SDON'TCRY bumped with an outer foe at the start and checked into the first turn, raced wellback along the inside and was never involved. JAZZY JAS raced off the pace in the four path early and was never a menace.
